 {"id":"asupersync-o8o","title":"[I/O] Implement AsyncRead Trait and Extensions","description":"# AsyncRead Trait Implementation

## Overview
Define and implement the AsyncRead trait for non-blocking read operations with obligation tracking.

## Core Trait

```rust
use std::io;
use std::pin::Pin;
use std::task::{Context, Poll};

/// Buffer for reading data
pub struct ReadBuf<'a> {
    buf: &'a mut [u8],
    filled: usize,
    initialized: usize,
}

impl<'a> ReadBuf<'a> {
    pub fn new(buf: &'a mut [u8]) -> Self {
        let initialized = buf.len(); // Assume initialized
        Self { buf, filled: 0, initialized }
    }

    pub fn filled(&self) -> &[u8] {
        &self.buf[..self.filled]
    }

    pub fn filled_mut(&mut self) -> &mut [u8] {
        &mut self.buf[..self.filled]
    }

    pub fn unfilled(&mut self) -> &mut [u8] {
        &mut self.buf[self.filled..]
    }

    pub fn put_slice(&mut self, src: &[u8]) {
        self.unfilled()[..src.len()].copy_from_slice(src);
        self.filled += src.len();
    }

    pub fn advance(&mut self, n: usize) {
        self.filled += n;
    }

    pub fn remaining(&self) -> usize {
        self.buf.len() - self.filled
    }
}

/// Async non-blocking read
pub trait AsyncRead {
    /// Attempt to read data into buf
    fn poll_read(
        self: Pin<&mut Self>,
        cx: &mut Context<'_>,
        buf: &mut ReadBuf<'_>,
    ) -> Poll<io::Result<()>>;
}
```

## Extension Trait

```rust
pub trait AsyncReadExt: AsyncRead {
    /// Read exact number of bytes
    fn read_exact<'a>(&'a mut self, buf: &'a mut [u8]) -> ReadExact<'a, Self>
    where
        Self: Unpin;

    /// Read to end of reader
    fn read_to_end<'a>(&'a mut self, buf: &'a mut Vec<u8>) -> ReadToEnd<'a, Self>
    where
        Self: Unpin;

    /// Read to string
    fn read_to_string<'a>(&'a mut self, buf: &'a mut String) -> ReadToString<'a, Self>
    where
        Self: Unpin;

    /// Read single byte
    fn read_u8(&mut self) -> ReadU8<'_, Self>
    where
        Self: Unpin;

    /// Chain readers
    fn chain<R: AsyncRead>(self, next: R) -> Chain<Self, R>
    where
        Self: Sized;

    /// Take at most n bytes
    fn take(self, limit: u64) -> Take<Self>
    where
        Self: Sized;
}
