 {"id":"asupersync-ohz8","title":"Implement TraceReplayer for Lab runtime","description":"## Overview

Implement the TraceReplayer that feeds recorded decisions back into the Lab runtime to achieve exact execution replay.

## Background

This is the core replay mechanism. Instead of making scheduling decisions, the Lab runtime in replay mode reads the next decision from the trace and executes it.

## Design Requirements

### Exact Replay
- Every scheduling decision must match recorded
- Time advances must match exactly
- I/O results must be replayed, not simulated fresh

### Divergence Detection
- If execution diverges from trace, detect and report
- Divergence means bug or trace corruption
- Provide helpful error message with divergence point

### Stepping Support
- Support "step to next event" for debugging
- Support "continue to breakpoint" (e.g., specific tick or task)
- Support "run to completion"

## Implementation

```rust
pub struct TraceReplayer {
    reader: TraceReader,
    current_index: usize,
    mode: ReplayMode,
}

pub enum ReplayMode {
    Run,                    // Run to completion
    Step,                   // Stop after each event
    RunTo(Breakpoint),      // Run to specific point
}

pub enum Breakpoint {
    Tick(u64),
    Task(TaskId),
    Event(usize),           // Event index
}

impl TraceReplayer {
    pub fn new(reader: TraceReader) -> Self;
    pub fn next_event(&mut self) -> Option<&TraceEvent>;
    pub fn verify_matches(&self, actual: &TraceEvent) -> Result<(), DivergenceError>;
}

pub struct DivergenceError {
    pub index: usize,
    pub expected: TraceEvent,
    pub actual: TraceEvent,
    pub context: String,
}
```

## Lab Runtime Integration

```rust
impl LabRuntime {
    pub fn replay(trace: TraceReader) -> ReplayRuntime;
}

pub struct ReplayRuntime {
    lab: LabRuntime,
    replayer: TraceReplayer,
}
